warmup.title: Cat-Cow Stretch
instruction: Start on all fours with hands under shoulders and knees under hips
Arch your back, lifting your head and tailbone towards the ceiling (Cow)
Round your spine, tucking your chin and tailbone towards your chest (Cat)
Alternate between the two positions in a slow and controlled manner
Repeat for the specified duration.

warmup.title: Dead Bug
instruction: Lie on your back with arms extended towards the ceiling and knees bent at 90 degrees
Lower one arm and the opposite leg towards the floor while keeping your core engaged
Return to the starting position and alternate sides
Repeat for the specified duration.

beginner.title: Basic Crunch
instruction: Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the ground
Place your hands streteched over your head
Lift your head, neck, and shoulders off the ground
Lower back down slowly
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

beginner.title: Plank
instruction: Start in a push-up position with your elbows bent and forearms on the ground
Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels
Hold the position while engaging your core
Avoid letting your hips sag or rise too high
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

intermediate.title: Bicycle Crunch
instruction: Lie on your back with your hands behind your head
Lift your shoulders off the ground and bring one elbow towards the opposite knee
Switch sides, mimicking a pedaling motion
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

intermediate.title: Mountain Climbers
instruction: Start in a push-up position with your hands under your shoulders
Bring one knee towards your chest and quickly switch legs
Keep your core engaged and back straight
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

advanced.title: crunch straight leg up
instruction: Lie down on your back with your legs perpendicular to the floor and arms extended over your shoulders.
Raise your torso off the floor and take your hands towards your feet.
Hold for a while, then slowly return to the starting position.
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

advanced.title: Dragon Flag
instruction: Lie on a bench or flat surface and grab the edge with both hands above your head
Lift your legs and hips off the bench, keeping your body straight
Slowly lower your legs back down without touching the surface
Maintain control throughout the movement
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

warmup.title: Cat Cow Stretch
instruction: Start on all fours, with knees under hips and wrists under shoulders
Take a deep breath in and as you do, lower your belly towards the floor and lift your chest and eyes towards the ceiling
Breathe out slowly through your mouth, round your spine towards the ceiling, tuck your tailbone under and drop your head
Breathe in and return to the starting position
Repeat for the specified duration.

warmup.title: Push-up (wall)
instruction: Stand facing the wall, extend your arms in front of you and place your palms flat on the wall at shoulder height and shoulder-width apart
Bend your elbows and bring your body towards the wall
Press your palms into the wall to push your body back to the starting position
Keep your body in a straight line throughout the movement
Repeat for the specified duration.

warmup.title: Roll Pec Foam Rolling
instruction: Lie face down and position the foam roller underneath your chest
Position your hands above your head, at shoulder width
Roll up and down from your lower sternum to your armpits
Repeat the motions for a specified period

beginner.title: Seal Push-Up
instruction: Start in a plank position with your hands under your shoulders and legs extended behind you.
Lower your body to the ground while keeping your elbows tucked close to your sides.
Push your upper body up while keeping your hips and legs relaxed on the ground.
Hold briefly, then return to the starting position.
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

beginner.title: Kneeling Push-Up
instruction: Start in a kneeling position with your hands flat on the floor, shoulder-width apart.
Keep your knees on the ground and your body in a straight line from head to knees.
Lower your chest towards the floor by bending your elbows.
Push yourself back up to the starting position.
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

beginner.title: Standard Push-Up
instruction: Start in a plank position with your hands under your shoulders and feet together.
Lower your body towards the floor by bending your elbows while keeping your body straight.
Push back up to the starting position.
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

intermediate.title: Standard Push-Up
instruction: Start in a plank position with your hands under your shoulders
Lower your chest to the floor while keeping your body straight
Push back up to the starting position
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

intermediate.title: Incline Push-Up
instruction: Place your hands on an elevated surface like a chair or bench
Keep your body in a straight line and lower your chest towards the surface
Push yourself back to the starting position
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

intermediate.title: Decline Push-Up
instruction: Place your feet on an elevated surface like a chair or bench
Keep your body in a straight line and lower your chest towards the floor
Push back up to the starting position
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

intermediate.title: Spider Crawl Push-Up
instruction: Start in a standard push-up position
As you lower your chest to the floor, bring one knee up towards your elbow
Push back up and alternate sides
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

advanced.title: Clock Push-Up
instruction: Start in a standard push-up position with your hands under your shoulders
Move one hand slightly forward (like moving around a clock) and perform a push-up
Alternate hand positions, moving clockwise after each push-up
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

advanced.title: Clap Push-Up
instruction: Start in a plank position with hands under your shoulders
Lower your chest to the floor and explosively push yourself up
Clap your hands together before landing back into the starting position
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

advanced.title: Archer Push-Up
instruction: Start in a wide push-up position with hands slightly wider than shoulder-width
Lower your chest toward one hand while keeping the other arm extended
Push back up to the starting position and alternate sides
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

advanced.title: Single Arm Push-Up on Knees
instruction: Start in a kneeling push-up position with your knees on the ground
Place one hand behind your back and the other under your shoulder
Lower your chest toward the floor and push back up
Switch sides after the specified sets and repetitions

warmup.title: High Knees
instruction: Stand straight with feet hip-width apart
Lift your knees to your chest while jogging in place
Keep your back straight and core engaged
Pump your arms to maintain balance and rhythm
Repeat for the set duration

warmup.title: Butt Kicks
instruction: Stand straight with feet shoulder-width apart
Jog in place while kicking your heels up to touch your glutes
Keep your arms bent and swing them naturally
Maintain a steady pace throughout the movement
Repeat for the set duration

warmup.title: Jogging in Place
instruction: Stand tall with feet hip-width apart
Begin jogging in place with light, quick steps
Keep your shoulders relaxed and swing your arms naturally
Focus on warming up your legs and increasing your heart rate
Repeat for the set duration

warmup.title: Side Lunges
instruction: Stand tall with feet hip-width apart and hands at your chest or hips.
Take a big step to the right, shifting your weight onto your right leg.
Bend your right knee while keeping your left leg straight and your back flat.
Push your hips back and lower until your right thigh is parallel to the floor.
Push off your right foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate sides and Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

beginner.title: Bodyweight Squat
instruction: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart
Keep your chest up and back straight
Lower your hips as if sitting in a chair
Push through your heels to stand back up
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

beginner.title: Wall Squat
instruction: Stand with your back against a wall
Slide down into a squat until your knees are at a 90-degree angle
Hold the position while keeping your back flat against the wall
Push through your heels to stand back up
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

beginner.title: Sumo Squat
instruction: Stand with feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointed out
Lower your hips straight down while keeping your chest up
Push through your heels to return to standing
Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

intermediate.title: Jump Squat
instruction: Start in a squat position with feet shoulder-width apart
Lower your hips and explode upwards into a jump
Land softly back into a squat position
Keep your core engaged throughout the movement
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

intermediate.title: Pulse Squat
instruction: Start in a squat position with feet shoulder-width apart
Lower into the squat and pulse up and down a few inches
Keep your back straight and core tight
Push through your heels to return to standing
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

intermediate.title: Bulgarian Split Squat
instruction: Stand in front of a bench or chair
Place one foot on the bench behind you
Lower your hips until your front thigh is parallel to the ground
Push through the front heel to return to standing
Switch legs and repeat for the specified sets and reps.

intermediate.title: Goblet Squat
instruction: Hold a weight close to your chest with both hands
Stand with feet shoulder-width apart
Lower into a squat, keeping the weight close to your chest
Push through your heels to stand back up
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

advanced.title: Bulgarian Split Squat
instruction: Stand in front of a bench or chair
Place one foot on the bench behind you
Lower your hips until your front thigh is parallel to the ground
Push through the front heel to return to standing
Switch legs and repeat for the specified sets and reps.

advanced.title: Goblet Squat
instruction: Hold a weight close to your chest with both hands
Stand with feet shoulder-width apart
Lower into a squat, keeping the weight close to your chest
Push through your heels to stand back up
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

advanced.title: Pistol Squat
instruction: Stand on one leg with the other leg extended straight in front of you
Lower into a squat on the supporting leg
Keep your core engaged and chest up
Push through your heel to stand back up
Repeat on the other leg

advanced.title: Cossack Squat
instruction: Stand with feet wide apart
Shift your weight to one leg and lower into a side squat
Keep the other leg extended straight with the toes pointing up
Push through the bent leg to return to standing
Alternate sides and repeat

warmup.title: Arm Circles
instruction: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart
Extend your arms out to your sides at shoulder height
Rotate your arms forward in small circles for 30 seconds
Reverse the direction and rotate backward for another 30 seconds

warmup.title: Chest-and-Front-of-Shoulder Stretch
instruction: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart near a doorway or wall corner
Place your forearm against the wall with your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle
Gently turn your body away from the wall until you feel a stretch in your chest and the front of your shoulder
Hold the stretch for 15â€“30 seconds, then switch sides
Breathe deeply and avoid overstretching

beginner.title: Front Arm Raises
instruction: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart
Hold a light object or bottle in each hand
Raise your arms straight out in front of you to shoulder height
Lower them back down slowly
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

beginner.title: Side Arm Raises
instruction: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart
Hold a light object or bottle in each hand
Raise your arms out to the sides to shoulder height
Lower them back down slowly
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

intermediate.title: Pike Push-Up
instruction: Start in a downward dog position with your hands and feet on the floor
Lower your head towards the ground by bending your elbows
Push back up to the starting position
Keep your core engaged throughout the movement
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

intermediate.title: Wall wide Push-Up
instruction: Stand facing the wall with your hands wider than your shoulders
Engage your core and lower your body towards the wall
Press your forearms against the wall
Push your body away from the wall until your arms are fully extended
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.

advanced.title: Handstand Hold
instruction: Stand facing a wall and place your hands on the floor shoulder-width apart
Kick your legs up to rest against the wall in a handstand position
Engage your shoulders and core to hold the position
Hold for the desired duration, then lower your legs carefully

advanced.title: Archer Push-Up
instruction: Start in a wide push-up position with hands slightly wider than shoulder-width
Lower your chest toward one hand while keeping the other arm extended
Push back up to the starting position and alternate sides
Repeat for the specified sets and reps.
